Hello! I’m Luna. As a UI/UX designer, I believe a button is never just a clickable rectangle—it’s a micro-interaction that guides the user, provides feedback, and establishes visual hierarchy. 

Below is a complete, modern, and accessible CSS button system. It uses CSS custom properties (design tokens) for easy theming, includes smooth micro-interactions, and prioritizes accessibility with proper focus states.

### 1. The HTML Structure
Always use the semantic `<button>` element for actions that trigger changes on the page, and `<a>` for navigation. 

```html
<div class="button-group">
  <!-- Primary: High emphasis, main call to action -->
  <button class="btn btn-primary">
    <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M5 12h14"/><path d="m12 5 7 7-7 7"/></svg>
    Get Started
  </button>

  <!-- Secondary: Medium emphasis, alternative actions -->
  <button class="btn btn-secondary">Learn More</button>

  <!-- Ghost: Low emphasis, tertiary actions or destructives -->
  <button class="btn btn-ghost">Cancel</button>

  <!-- Disabled State -->
  <button class="btn btn-primary" disabled>Processing...</button>
</div>
```

### 2. The CSS Implementation
This code is clean, scalable, and uses modern CSS features.

```css
/* =========================================
   1. DESIGN TOKENS (Variables)
   ========================================= */
:root {
  /* Colors */
  --color-primary: #4F46E5;       /* Indigo 600 */
  --color-primary-hover: #4338CA; /* Indigo 700 */
  --color-primary-active: #3730A3;/* Indigo 800 */
  --color-text-inverse: #FFFFFF;

  --color-surface: #FFFFFF;
  --color-border: #D1D5DB;        /* Gray 300 */
  --color-border-hover: #9CA3AF;  /* Gray 400 */
  --color-text-base: #374151;     /* Gray 700 */
  --color-ghost-hover: #F3F4F6;   /* Gray 100 */

  /* Typography & Spacing */
  --font-family: 'Inter', system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif;
  --font-weight-medium: 500;
  --radius-md: 8px;

  /* Effects */
  --shadow-sm: 0 1px 2px 0 rgb(0 0 0 / 0.05);
  --shadow-primary: 0 4px 14px 0 rgb(79 70 229 / 0.25);
  --ring-focus: 0 0 0 3px rgba(79, 70, 229, 0.4);

  /* Animation */
  --transition-fast: 150ms cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1);
}

/* =========================================
   2. BASE BUTTON STYLES
   ========================================= */
.btn {
  /* Layout */
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  gap: 0.5rem; /* Space for icons */

  /* Sizing */
  padding: 0.625rem 1.25rem; /* 10px 20px */
  min-height: 44px; /* Apple's recommended minimum touch target */

  /* Typography */
  font-family: var(--font-family);
  font-size: 0.875rem; /* 14px */
  font-weight: var(--font-weight-medium);
  line-height: 1.25;
  text-decoration: none;
  white-space: nowrap;

  /* Visuals */
  border-radius: var(--radius-md);
  border: 1px solid transparent;
  cursor: pointer;
  user-select: none;

  /* UX & Accessibility */
  transition: all var(--transition-fast);
  touch-action: manipulation; /* Removes 300ms tap delay on mobile */
  -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;
}

/* =========================================
   3. VARIANTS
   ========================================= */

/* Primary Button */
.btn-primary {
  background-color: var(--color-primary);
  color: var(--color-text-inverse);
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
}

.btn-primary:hover {
  background-color: var(--color-primary-hover);
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-primary);
  transform: translateY(-1px); /* Subtle lift */
}

.btn-primary:active {
  background-color: var(--color-primary-active);
  transform: translateY(0);
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
}

/* Secondary Button */
.btn-secondary {
  background-color: var(--color-surface);
  color: var(--color-text-base);
  border-color: var(--color-border);
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
}

.btn-secondary:hover {
  background-color: var(--color-ghost-hover);
  border-color: var(--color-border-hover);
}

.btn-secondary:active {
  background-color: #E5E7EB; /* Gray 200 */
}

/* Ghost Button */
.btn-ghost {
  background-color: transparent;
  color: var(--color-text-base);
}

.btn-ghost:hover {
  background-color: var(--color-ghost-hover);
}

.btn-ghost:active {
  background-color: #E5E7EB;
}

/* =========================================
   4. STATES (Focus & Disabled)
   ========================================= */

/* Accessible Focus State (Only shows for keyboard users) */
.btn:focus-visible {
  outline: none;
  box-shadow: var(--ring-focus);
}

/* Disabled State */
.btn:disabled {
  opacity: 0.5;
  cursor: not-allowed;
  pointer-events: none; /* Prevents hover effects */
  box-shadow: none;
  transform: none;
}

/* =========================================
   5. UTILITY / LAYOUT
   ========================================= */
.button-group {
  display: flex;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  gap: 1rem;
  padding: 2rem;
}
```

### 🧠 Luna's UX & Design Rationale:

1. **The 44px Touch Target:** The `min-height: 44px` ensures the button is easily tappable on mobile devices, adhering to WCAG accessibility guidelines and Apple's Human Interface Guidelines.
2. **`focus-visible` over `focus`:** Using `:focus-visible` ensures that the focus ring only appears when a user is navigating via keyboard (Tab key). Mouse users won't see an annoying blue outline when clicking, but keyboard users retain vital navigation feedback.
3. **Micro-interactions:** The primary button features a subtle `translateY(-1px)` and an expanded colored shadow on hover. This provides a tactile, "pressable" feel that delights users without being distracting.
4. **`touch-action: manipulation`:** This is a crucial, often-forgotten CSS property. It tells mobile browsers that the user is only clicking, not double-tapping to zoom, instantly removing the 300ms tap delay on older mobile browsers.
5. **Visual Hierarchy:** By providing Primary (filled), Secondary (outlined), and Ghost (text-only) variants, you guide the user's eye to the most important action on the screen while keeping secondary actions accessible but unobtrusive.

**Pro-Tip for Implementation:** If you are using this in a framework like React or Vue, I highly recommend converting the CSS variables into your global theme configuration (like Tailwind's `theme.extend` or CSS-in-JS tokens) to maintain a single source of truth across your application!
